data.enText: to lift, pull or throw sb/sth very heavy with one great effort

data.chText: 我用力把箱子弄下楼梯。
data.enText: I managed to heave the trunk down the stairs.

data.chText: 他们使劲把尸体从船上抛入水中。
data.enText: They heaved the body overboard.

data.chText: 我们大家一起用力拉绳子。
data.enText: We all heaved on the rope.
to rise up and down with strong, regular movements

data.chText: 小船在他们脚下颠簸着。
data.enText: The boat heaved beneath them.
Her shoulders heaved with laughter.
to make a sound slowly and often with effort

data.chText: 我们都如释重负地舒了一口气。
data.enText: We all heaved a sigh of relief .
to experience the tight feeling in your stomach that you get before you vomit
The thought of it makes me heave.
heave into sight/view
to appear, especially when moving gradually closer from a long way off
A ship hove into sight.

data.text: Hove is usually used for the past tense and past participle in this idiom.
这个习语通常用hove作过去式及过去分词。

data.enText: heave to
if a ship or its crew (= the people sailing it) heave to , the ship stops moving

data.text: Hove is usually used for the past tense and past participle in this phrasal verb.
这个短语动词通常用hove作过去式及过去分词。

data.enText: an act of lifting, pulling or throwing

data.chText: 他用劲一举，把大麻袋扔到卡车上。
data.enText: With a mighty heave he lifted the sack onto the truck.
a rising and falling movement
the steady heave of the sea
heave into sight/view
to appear, especially when moving gradually closer from a long way off
A ship hove into sight.

data.text: Hove is usually used for the past tense and past participle in this idiom.
这个习语通常用hove作过去式及过去分词。

data.enText: heave to
if a ship or its crew (= the people sailing it) heave to , the ship stops moving

data.text: Hove is usually used for the past tense and past participle in this phrasal verb.
这个短语动词通常用hove作过去式及过去分词。

example: he gave it a mighty heave
he was not good at heaving passes
he responded with a lift of his eyebrow
fireman learn several different raises for getting ladders up

tr: an involuntary spasm of ineffectual vomiting
example: a bad case of the heaves

tr: the act of lifting something with great effort
an upward movement (especially a rhythmical rising and falling)
example: the heaving of waves on a rough sea

tr: breathe noisily, as when one is exhausted
example: The runners reached the finish line, panting heavily

tr: make an unsuccessful effort to vomit
bend out of shape, as under pressure or from heat
example: The highway buckled during the heat wave

tr: utter a sound, as with obvious effort
example: She heaved a deep sigh when she saw the list of things to do

tr: rise and move, as in waves or billows
move or cause to move in a specified way, direction, or position

value.boxr_value: The forms heaves, heaving, heaved are used for meanings 1 to 4, and for the phrasal verb. The forms heaves, heaving, hove are used for meaning 5. 变化形式 heaves、heaving 和 heaved 用于义项1至4及短语动词。变化形式heaves、heaving 和 hove 用于义项5。

value.def: If you heave something heavy or difficult to move somewhere, you push, pull, or lift it using a lot of effort.

example.ex: It took five strong men to heave the statue up a ramp and lower it into place...
example.tran: 靠了5个强壮的男子才将雕像拉上坡道，再下放到合适的位置。

example.ex: He heaved Barney to his feet...
He heaved himself up off his stool.
It took only one heave to hurl him into the river.
example.tran: 只一推，就把他推进了河里。

value.def: If something heaves, it moves up and down with large regular movements.

example.ex: His chest heaved, and he took a deep breath.
example.tran: 他的胸脯上下起伏，然后他深深地吸了口气。

value.def: If you heave, or if your stomach heaves, you vomit or feel sick.

example.ex: He gasped and heaved and vomited again...
example.tran: 他又开始又喘又吐起来。

example.ex: My stomach heaved and I felt sick.
example.tran: 我的胃翻腾起来，直想呕吐。

value.def: If you heave a sigh, you give a big sigh.

example.ex: Mr Collier heaved a sigh and got to his feet.
example.tran: 科利尔先生深叹一口气，站了起来。

value.def: If a place is heaving or if it is heaving with people, it is full of people.

example.ex: The Happy Bunny club was heaving...
Father Auberon's Academy Club positively heaved with dashing young men.
example.tran: 父亲奥伯龙的“学院俱乐部”里真的是有为青年济济一堂。

value.def: When something heaves into view or heaves into sight, it appears.

example.ex: The train that now hove into view was clearly of a much older vintage.
example.tran: 现在进入视野的火车显然是一种古老得多的车型。
